review_blob: A very good pale ale.  I was very plesently surprised.  A delicious beer that I will buy again.
My absolute favorite stout beer.  Good to have when you are really hungry.  Has a nice flavor, especially when it has a slight chill.

This was a nice beer.  I enjoyed the six pack that I had, and I would buy it again.  Nice, smooth finish, and it wasnt too heavy in my stomach.  I plan on visiting the brewery, as I live in Hampton, VA.

Terrible pale ale.  As an avid beer drinker, I cannot think of any other beer that I have ever had that was worse than this one.  I bought a six pack at the grocery store, and, if I could have, I would have returned it.  Just absolutely aweful.
A decent holiday beer.  I purchased it in a variety pack, and even though I have enjoyed the one bottle that I got, I wouldnt want another one.
This is one of my favorites!  Just a delicious beer with good flavor, color, palate, etc.  It is easy to drink (sometimes too easy) and is great anytime.

One of the greatest beers ever, but can only be appreciated by a true beer drinker.  I remember the first time I tasted this; it tasted like motor oil.  Since then, I have learned to love it, and it is a well-earned treat!
Come on!  Dont be a beer snob.  There is nothing wrong with Miller Lite.  A good beer to drink while working in the yard, watching a game, etc.  It isnt gourmet, but it does the job.
A very delicious beer.  I liked the fact that it was easy to drink.  I recommend this beer for any Ale fan.
WOW!!   This beer is good.  I cant believe I got a buzz off of one bottle.  I must be losing my edge.
